S316 Code review fixes applied to Story 4B.7 (Host Settings & 5th Player Handling) - UI visibility improvement, test coverage additions, and bugfixes (Apr 5 at 6:36 PM)
**Investigated**: Five issues identified during code review: room settings panel visibility restricted to host-only (AC6 violation), missing error handling test coverage for table-full edge cases, missing settings persistence test assertions, double-counting bug in rematch missing-seats calculation, and missing test for spectator placeholder component.

**Learned**: RoomSettingsPanel visibility was incorrectly scoped inside v-if="isHost" conditional, preventing non-hosts from viewing settings in lobby despite :can-edit prop controlling editability. Missing seats calculation in handleRematch used arithmetic on set sizes (deadSeatPlayerIds + departedPlayerIds) which double-counts players in both sets; correct approach filters room.players for eligible seats (connected AND not dead AND not departed). WebSocket mocks in Vitest require ES6 class constructor pattern, not vi.fn().mockImplementation() pattern.

